  <%- include('partials/site-header', { current: 'privacy' }) %>
  <main class="page-main">
    <section class="page-hero site-shell"><span class="eyebrow">Plain-language privacy</span><h1 class="page-title">Privacy Policy</h1><p class="page-lede">This policy explains what Claude2PDF processes, where that processing happens and what is stored. It is written to match the current product architecture.</p></section>
    <div class="legal-wrap"><div class="legal-meta"><span>Effective: June 19, 2026</span><span>No account required</span><span>No advertising analytics</span></div><article class="legal-doc">
      <h2>1. Scope</h2><p>This Privacy Policy applies to the Claude2PDF website and conversion service. Claude2PDF converts public conversation share pages from supported AI platforms into a browser-rendered document that you can save as a PDF.</p>
      <h2>2. Public share links and conversation content</h2><p>When you submit a supported public share URL, your browser sends that URL to Claude2PDF's <code>/api/extract</code> endpoint. The server temporarily opens the public page with an automated browser and returns the rendered HTML to your browser so the conversation can be parsed.</p><ul><li>The application code does not intentionally save the public share URL or conversation HTML to a database.</li><li>The application does not sign into your AI account or access private conversations.</li><li>Public share links may be accessible to anyone who has the URL. Do not submit a link that contains information you are not authorized to process or export.</li><li>Hosting and network providers may process basic request metadata such as IP address, timestamp, headers and error information as part of normal infrastructure operation.</li></ul>
      <h2>3. Browser session storage</h2><p>Claude2PDF uses browser <code>sessionStorage</code> to move the source URL, parsed conversation and conversion status between the home, loading and preview pages. This data is scoped to the browser session and is cleared when you start another conversion, when the application removes it, or when the browser session ends. Claude2PDF does not use <code>localStorage</code> for conversation history.</p>
      <h2>4. PDF generation</h2><p>The preview and PDF template are rendered in your browser. The Download PDF action uses the browser's print function. Claude2PDF does not receive or store the finished PDF file.</p>
      <h2>5. Feedback data</h2><p>If you submit feedback, Claude2PDF may collect:</p><ul><li>a star rating;</li><li>your feedback message;</li><li>an optional email address;</li><li>whether you consented to receive product updates;</li><li>the detected provider, page URL, application version and browser user-agent string.</li></ul><p>Feedback is sent through the Claude2PDF server to a Google Apps Script endpoint and stored in a private Google Sheet controlled by the operator. If delivery to Google fails, the server may place the submission in a local fallback queue so it is not lost. That fallback can contain the same feedback fields, including an email address if you provided one.</p><p>An email address is optional. It may be used for product updates only when you explicitly opt in. It may also be used to respond to your feedback or process a privacy request.</p>
      <h2>6. Cookies and analytics</h2><p>At the time of this policy, Claude2PDF does not set advertising cookies and does not include a behavioral analytics product. The app uses session storage for the active conversion flow. Third-party resources or pages may apply their own technologies and policies.</p>
      <h2>7. Third-party services</h2><p>Claude2PDF relies on or links to third parties:</p><ul><li><strong>Source AI platforms:</strong> Claude, ChatGPT, Gemini and Grok host the public pages you ask Claude2PDF to retrieve.</li><li><strong>Google services:</strong> Google Fonts are used for typography, and Google Apps Script/Sheets are used for feedback storage.</li><li><strong>Tailwind CDN:</strong> the home interface currently loads Tailwind CSS from a content-delivery network.</li><li><strong>Buy Me a Coffee:</strong> the support button opens an external page only when you choose to visit it.</li><li><strong>Hosting infrastructure:</strong> the application and extraction server run on a hosting provider that processes normal network and operational data.</li></ul><p>Each third party controls its own processing. Review the policies of the service you use.</p>
      <h2>8. Retention</h2><p>Conversation content is processed transiently and is not intentionally retained by the application server. Browser session data follows the session lifecycle described above. Feedback records may be kept while they are useful for product improvement, support or update communications, and are deleted when no longer needed. Fallback feedback records may remain until they are delivered, reviewed or manually removed.</p>
      <h2>9. Security</h2><p>Claude2PDF uses input validation, request rate limits and HTTPS when deployed on its production host. No online service can guarantee absolute security. Use only public share links and avoid exporting material that you are not comfortable processing through a web service.</p>
      <h2>10. Your choices and requests</h2><p>You can avoid providing an email, decline update communications and clear browser session data by closing the tab or clearing site data. To request access, correction or deletion of feedback data, submit a feedback message with the request and the same email address used in the original submission. Additional verification may be required.</p>
      <h2>11. Children</h2><p>Claude2PDF is not directed to children under 13. Do not submit personal information about a child unless you have the legal authority to do so.</p>
      <h2>12. Changes</h2><p>This policy may change when the product architecture, providers or legal requirements change. The effective date at the top will be updated when material revisions are made.</p>
      <h2>13. Questions</h2><p>Questions about this policy can be submitted through the feedback form available after a conversion.</p>
      <p class="legal-note">Claude2PDF is an independent tool and is not affiliated with, endorsed by or operated by Anthropic, OpenAI, Google or xAI.</p>
    </article></div>
